aim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Henri de Lindsay was born in 1020, in Normandy, France. He had at least 1 daughter with Countess Adeline de Warenne."},"et":{"1020–":"1020–Surnud","1025–Female":"1025–Surnud","1150–1220":"1150–1220","1020–Male":"1020–Surnud","1025":"1025","1220":"1220","1020":"1020","1150":"1150","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Normandy?":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1020–":"1020–Kuollut","1025–Female":"1025–Kuollut","1150–1220":"1150–1220","1020–Male":"1020–Kuollut","1025":"1025","1220":"1220","1020":"1020","1150":"1150","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Normandy?":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1020–":"1020–Décédé","1025–Female":"1025–Décédée","1150–1220":"1150–1220","1020–Male":"1020–Décédé","1025":"1025","1220":"1220","1020":"1020","1150":"1150","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Écosse","Normandy?":"Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Henri de Lindsay est né en 1020, à Normandie, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Countess Adeline de Warenne."},"de":{"1020–":"1020–Verstorben","1025–Female":"1025–Verstorben","1150–1220":"1150–1220","1020–Male":"1020–Verstorben","1025":"1025","1220":"1220","1020":"1020","1150":"1150","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Normandy?":"Normandie, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Henri de Lindsay wurde 1020 in Normandie, Frankreich geboren. Er hatte mit Countess Adeline de Warenne mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"1020–":"1020–Desede","1025–Female":"1025–Desede","1150–1220":"1150–1220","1020–Male":"1020–Desede","1025":"1025","1220":"1220","1020